00:16:12,001 --> 00:16:16,508
I always felt there was a fatal element
of hunger in your last affair.

225
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:18,521
That's not true.

226
00:16:18,617 --> 00:16:22,069
I don't think Jeff would have run
quite so quickly back to his wife...

227
00:16:22,356 --> 00:16:24,946
.. if he didn't feel a certain pressure.

228
00:16:25,138 --> 00:16:26,481
I sensed it.

229
00:16:26,768 --> 00:16:30,796
His name was Jack. And you were never
here, so you don't know what happened.

230
00:16:31,467 --> 00:16:34,248
Darling, don't be so defensive.

231
00:16:34,919 --> 00:16:37,700
I base this observation
on the time I saw you together.

232
00:16:37,988 --> 00:16:43,071
And I'm not saying anything different than
those high-priced psychiatrists have said.

233
00:16:43,455 --> 00:16:47,386
When it comes to men, you're probably
doing something to stand in your way.

234
00:16:47,769 --> 00:16:49,687
- I probably am.
- Yeah.

235
00:16:49,879 --> 00:16:53,139
Well, this is out.
Looks like I'm going to a luau !

236
00:16:54,961 --> 00:16:57,071
Oh, my God. Look at me.

237
00:16:59,276 --> 00:17:01,290
I gotta redo my whole make-up.

238
00:17:06,372 --> 00:17:08,193
It's hell, gettin' older.

239
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:12,126
Especially when you feel 21 inside.

240
00:17:17,016 --> 00:17:20,181
All the strengths that sustain you
all through your life...

241
00:17:20,469 --> 00:17:23,633
.. just vanish one by one.

242
00:17:26,606 --> 00:17:29,388
And you study your face
in the mirror and you...

243
00:17:35,524 --> 00:17:37,826
You notice something is missing.

244
00:17:40,702 --> 00:17:43,004
And then you realise it's your future.

245
00:17:49,044 --> 00:17:50,963
So that's...

246
00:17:51,826 --> 00:17:54,798
That's why I want you to find yourself...

247
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:57,867
.. while there's still time left to enjoy it.

248
00:17:57,867 --> 00:18:00,744
- Hi.
- Hi.

249
00:18:25,772 --> 00:18:28,936
- I guess I'm early.
- The guests haven't arrived yet.

250
00:18:32,197 --> 00:18:35,361
Well, you look wonderful, all dressed up.

251
00:18:36,608 --> 00:18:38,429
It's starting to rain.

252
00:18:39,676 --> 00:18:41,499
Maybe it'll cool things off.

253
00:18:42,649 --> 00:18:44,472
Let's hope.

254
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:55,020
Well, you look lovely.
I said that !

255
00:18:55,211 --> 00:18:57,130
Thank you.

256
00:18:58,856 --> 00:19:01,061
- Did you know the, um...
- Steffie...

257
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:05,952
- Sorry. What were you gonna say ?
- No. What ?

258
00:19:06,335 --> 00:19:09,116
- You looked like you were...
- No, nothing.

259
00:19:09,116 --> 00:19:11,993
Thunder's getting close.

260
00:19:14,390 --> 00:19:16,116
Yeah.

261
00:19:18,705 --> 00:19:21,390
So, who's the history professor ?

262
00:19:21,678 --> 00:19:25,705
The history professor ? How did you know
about that ? Did we talk about that ?

263
00:19:25,994 --> 00:19:30,405
Well, you mentioned to me one time that
that might be the title of your book.

264
00:19:31,747 --> 00:19:34,048
The history professor was my father.

265
00:19:36,445 --> 00:19:39,706
He taught at a college
in Connecticut and he...

266
00:19:41,145 --> 00:19:43,159
.. he was fired during the McCarthy era.

267
00:19:43,351 --> 00:19:46,707
He was blacklisted. He had to do
all kinds of things to keep us going.

268
00:19:46,898 --> 00:19:48,433
Like what ?

269
00:19:48,625 --> 00:19:52,748
He supported us by playing poker
and betting the horses.

270
00:19:53,036 --> 00:19:54,953
He sounds wonderful.

271
00:19:55,241 --> 00:19:57,063
Yeah, he was.

272
00:19:58,980 --> 00:20:01,090
I see what you mean by a survivor.

273
00:20:06,268 --> 00:20:08,377
This summer went by too fast.

274
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:14,324
I had such high hopes for this book.

275
00:20:15,379 --> 00:20:17,392
To tell you the truth, I'm floundering.

276
00:20:17,392 --> 00:20:20,269
Is this the first time
you've tried to write a book ?

277
00:20:25,064 --> 00:20:29,572
Oh, I've published a couple of short
stories. Nothing... Nothing any good.

278
00:20:31,201 --> 00:20:35,516
I've never been able to do it full time. I've
always been busy with other obligations.

279
00:20:38,202 --> 00:20:40,311
You don't want to hear about all this.

280
00:20:40,598 --> 00:20:43,858
You know, Lane showed me
some of your short stories and...

281
00:20:44,146 --> 00:20:46,064
.. I thought they were wonderful.

282
00:20:47,599 --> 00:20:49,420
It's funny.

283
00:20:50,379 --> 00:20:52,584
I've wanted to talk to you so often,...

284
00:20:53,831 --> 00:20:55,845
.. but we never seem to be alone.

285
00:20:57,092 --> 00:20:59,969
We were alone.
We were alone for a whole afternoon.

286
00:21:01,024 --> 00:21:04,860
Running into you at the local
flea market is not exactly private.

287
00:21:05,626 --> 00:21:08,791
Well, we walked around together.
You didn't say anything.

288
00:21:08,983 --> 00:21:10,804
No, I didn't, did I ?

289
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:14,162
Well, I felt awkward.

290
00:21:17,326 --> 00:21:22,025
At least you liked the record I found you
so it wasn't a complete waste of time.

291
00:21:22,312 --> 00:21:26,436
It's so funny because I used to be in love
with a boy who just idolised Art Tatum.

292
00:21:26,723 --> 00:21:30,079
Well, this was years ago
on my first visit to Paris.

293
00:21:30,367 --> 00:21:34,970
He was a student and he played piano
in a jazz club in the student quarter.

294
00:21:35,449 --> 00:21:37,270
He didn't speak any English.

295
00:21:38,134 --> 00:21:41,970
And we spent a summer trying to make
each other understand our feelings.

296
00:21:42,162 --> 00:21:45,806
The funny thing was it didn't matter
that we only knew a few words.

297
00:21:46,189 --> 00:21:49,066
Oh, anyway, that was years ago.

298
00:21:49,066 --> 00:21:51,943
I hate thunder. I don't care how harmless
it is, I wanna get under the bed !

299
00:21:55,971 --> 00:21:58,752
- The air is full of electricity.
- I'm serious !

300
00:21:59,136 --> 00:22:01,245
- Where is everyone ? I heard voices.
- Hi.

301
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:03,835
- How do I look ? Don't say "old and fat".
- Great.

302
00:22:04,121 --> 00:22:06,423
Great. What time
do the guests arrive ?

303
00:22:06,711 --> 00:22:10,834
Any minute. Let's get some more lights
on. Did Lane make any hors d'oeuvres ?

304
00:22:12,369 --> 00:22:14,478
What were you two doing
before we came down ?

305
00:22:14,765 --> 00:22:16,396
Excuse me ? What ?

306
00:22:16,684 --> 00:22:19,944
I hope you weren't out on the porch.
That lightning's getting close.

307
00:22:20,327 --> 00:22:21,574
- Oh, no.
- No.

308
00:22:21,766 --> 00:22:24,546
- Let's have some music.
- All right. Who wants what ?

309
00:22:24,834 --> 00:22:28,670
- Well, you know about me. Peter ?
- Vodka.

310
00:22:28,862 --> 00:22:31,643
- Stephanie, what do you want ?
- Vodka, please.

311
00:22:32,026 --> 00:22:34,616
Have you given any more thought
about my memoirs ?

312
00:22:34,808 --> 00:22:39,219
They deserve better than me. They're
too good to waste on a fledgling writer.

313
00:22:39,602 --> 00:22:41,808
You're patronising me.

314
00:22:42,096 --> 00:22:45,644
- Lane says you think my life is trivial.
- I never said that.

315
00:22:45,644 --> 00:22:48,521
- Lloyd, come on, dance with me.
- Oh, honey, I'm such a stiff.

316
00:22:51,973 --> 00:22:55,041
If you can figure out the universe,
you can figure out the box step.

317
00:22:55,424 --> 00:22:57,247
All right.

318
00:23:00,699 --> 00:23:02,904
See, there ? You're terrific.

319
00:23:03,191 --> 00:23:05,014
- I try.

320
00:23:18,919 --> 00:23:21,028
I had so many things
I wanted to say to you.

321
00:23:21,219 --> 00:23:26,015
Oh, well, it's, you know... There are
people coming over and people here, so...

322
00:23:26,303 --> 00:23:28,796
- I don't wanna be pushy.
- No, you're not pushy.

323
00:23:29,084 --> 00:23:31,385
I wish you'd been here
for the whole summer.

324
00:23:31,577 --> 00:23:35,700
Yeah, well, I couldn't.
I have obligations, too, so...

325
00:23:36,084 --> 00:23:38,194
What is that record ? Lt's terrific !

326
00:23:38,385 --> 00:23:40,303
It's Art Tatum and Ben Webster.

327
00:23:42,029 --> 00:23:43,563
- It's funny.
- What ?

328
00:23:43,658 --> 00:23:46,152
I made a complete fool
out of myself when I met you.

329
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:49,508
- No ! You didn't.
- I remember carrying on at great length...

330
00:23:49,796 --> 00:23:52,480
.. about writing and metaphor and choice.

331
00:23:52,672 --> 00:23:57,468
- I left no cliché unturned.
- No. Actually I just... No, I...

332
00:23:57,755 --> 00:23:59,769
I just thought you were so sweet.

333
00:24:01,687 --> 00:24:06,098
You reminded me of Paul,
the boy that I knew in Paris.

334
00:24:06,961 --> 00:24:08,879
- Really ?
- Yeah.

335
00:24:10,125 --> 00:24:12,140
- Yeah.
- Well, I'm very flattered.

336
00:24:12,332 --> 00:24:15,688
Which one is Art Tatum
and which is Ben Webster ?

337
00:24:15,879 --> 00:24:17,798
Art Tatum's the piano.

338
00:24:19,427 --> 00:24:22,400
See, and I always felt foolish
all the time because...

339
00:24:22,592 --> 00:24:24,893
- Why ?
- .. I was very taken with you right off.

340
00:24:25,181 --> 00:24:29,304
I love all the music from that era. You
don't have any Benny Goodman, do you ?

341
00:24:29,592 --> 00:24:31,318
Uh, not here.

342
00:24:31,606 --> 00:24:33,811
Or Coon-Sanders Nighthawks ?

343
00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:39,181
- Now, please don't panic when I say this.
- No.

344
00:24:39,372 --> 00:24:42,058
I just think that you're incredibly lovely.

345
00:24:43,593 --> 00:24:48,003
Peter, don't. Don't, please.
Let's just stop this before it's too late.

346
00:24:48,291 --> 00:24:50,401
You know, I can't.

347
00:24:50,592 --> 00:24:55,003
I just... I just feel flushed
and... and my heart is pounding.

348
00:24:56,155 --> 00:24:58,936
- - Oh, there are the Richmonds.

349
00:24:59,224 --> 00:25:01,045
Get it, will you, Lloyd ?

350
00:25:03,827 --> 00:25:06,415
- Oh, Howard !
- Oh, it's pouring out there.

351
00:25:06,607 --> 00:25:09,579
We were expecting the Richmonds.
Let me get you a drink.

352
00:25:09,771 --> 00:25:13,511
Hi, Howard. Hi. Oh, the Richmonds
must be stuck. You're wet.

353
00:25:13,894 --> 00:25:15,333
Yes, I know.

354
00:25:16,004 --> 00:25:19,264
Look, my old Ouija board ! Look !

355
00:25:19,456 --> 00:25:22,620
They take too long. What you want
is a computerised Ouija board.

356
00:25:23,004 --> 00:25:25,978
That way you can punch up
any dead person you wanna talk to.

357
00:25:26,170 --> 00:25:29,334
- Howard, you did say Scotch ?
- Ask Lane to dance with you.

358
00:25:29,622 --> 00:25:31,539
- Me ?
- Mm-hm. She'll be thrilled.

359
00:25:31,827 --> 00:25:33,937
- She's got a big crush on you.
- I don't dance.

360
00:25:34,128 --> 00:25:37,868
That's what everybody says.
Come on. She's been so blue.

361
00:25:38,156 --> 00:25:39,977
- Lane ?
- Yes ?

362
00:25:40,265 --> 00:25:42,184
Go ahead. Go ahead !

363
00:25:42,472 --> 00:25:45,636
Uh, Lane, uh, Peter was just asking me...

364
00:25:46,019 --> 00:25:48,417
.. if I'd ask you to dance with him.

365
00:25:49,183 --> 00:25:51,197
Oh ! No, thank you.

366
00:25:51,485 --> 00:25:55,321
Oh, yes, thank you.
That music is fabulous !

367
00:25:55,608 --> 00:25:58,389
I used to go to Harlem
to hear music like that.

368
00:25:58,581 --> 00:26:01,842
I was dating a disc jockey.
He used to call records "sides".

369
00:26:02,033 --> 00:26:03,855
- - I have two left feet.

370
00:26:04,142 --> 00:26:07,306
I'll get that. I'll get it.
You just enjoy yourselves.

371
00:26:07,306 --> 00:26:10,184
- Is she bothering you ?
- No, not at all.

372
00:26:12,773 --> 00:26:15,937
- I like her energy.
- It's the record you got at the flea market.

373
00:26:16,129 --> 00:26:18,911
- I didn't know you liked jazz.
- You like Prokofiev.

374
00:26:19,198 --> 00:26:20,924
Yeah, but not to dance to.

375
00:26:21,691 --> 00:26:24,089
The Richmonds aren't coming.
Their house is flooded.

376
00:26:24,377 --> 00:26:26,774
Really ? Then maybe
we can go to the Kurosawa film.

377
00:26:27,062 --> 00:26:29,938
- In this storm ?
- Well, you know, maybe.

378
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:32,048
Let's not let it kill our evening.

379
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:35,596
The Richmonds aren't coming.
We're lucky. They're so boring !

380
00:26:35,980 --> 00:26:39,527
- Then why did you invite them ?
- Uh-oh. Oh, God !

381
00:26:39,815 --> 00:26:42,309
- This could last for hours.
- Lloyd.

382
00:26:42,501 --> 00:26:46,144
- Just light some candles.
- OK. I'll get some matches.

383
00:26:46,336 --> 00:26:49,021
I love walking around
in the pitch-black.

384
00:26:49,308 --> 00:26:51,226
I think I put my hand in the guacamole.

385
00:26:51,418 --> 00:26:55,446
Lloyd ! The Richmonds are
flooded, the electricity's gone off.

386
00:26:55,734 --> 00:26:59,857
God is testing us and l, for one,
am gonna be ready. Where's the vodka ?

387
00:26:59,857 --> 00:27:02,734
T.

388
00:27:47,996 --> 00:27:49,914
O.

389
00:27:54,708 --> 00:27:56,435
M.

390
00:27:57,202 --> 00:27:59,024
I don't know any Toms.

391
00:28:00,174 --> 00:28:02,092
Oh, wait a minute.

392
00:28:02,668 --> 00:28:07,079
Are you that dentist in Hackensack
that tried to rape me when I was 15 ?

393
00:28:08,326 --> 00:28:10,147
No ? OK.

394
00:28:11,586 --> 00:28:13,407
OK.

395
00:28:13,599 --> 00:28:15,421
One more try.

396
00:28:15,421 --> 00:28:18,297
N.

397
00:28:23,763 --> 00:28:25,585
Ooh, I.

398
00:28:28,846 --> 00:28:29,710
C.

399
00:28:29,997 --> 00:28:32,202
Oh, God. Nick.

400
00:28:33,641 --> 00:28:35,942
Wait a minute. Are you in this room ?

401
00:28:36,230 --> 00:28:39,969
Is your ghost in this room,
bullet hole an' all ?

402
00:28:42,272 --> 00:28:44,190
You were so bad.

403
00:28:45,052 --> 00:28:46,875
But so gorgeous.

404
00:28:48,984 --> 00:28:52,245
Do you still comb your hair
like you were in Sicily ?

405
00:28:55,121 --> 00:28:57,039
Well, we had some good times.

406
00:28:59,340 --> 00:29:01,162
It was hectic.

407
00:29:02,313 --> 00:29:04,134
It was dangerous.

408
00:29:06,532 --> 00:29:08,354
And then it ended.

409
00:29:18,999 --> 00:29:21,012
I think it's clearing up.

410
00:29:22,354 --> 00:29:24,081
Yeah ?

411
00:29:37,986 --> 00:29:39,999
Please don't move away from here.

412
00:29:44,314 --> 00:29:46,232
I have to.

413
00:29:49,396 --> 00:29:53,136
You know, I should never drink.
My head really spins.

414
00:29:53,903 --> 00:29:55,726
How are you gonna drive home ?

415
00:29:56,972 --> 00:29:58,794
Same way I always do:

416
00:29:59,945 --> 00:30:01,767
.. thinking about you.

417
00:30:05,028 --> 00:30:09,630
You know, in all the time I've known you
I don't think I've ever seen you drink.

418
00:30:10,013 --> 00:30:11,453
No.

419
00:30:12,604 --> 00:30:15,864
Although the year after my wife died
I was never sober.

420
00:30:18,453 --> 00:30:23,918
Of course, on the faculty of the school
where I work, it's... hard to tell.

421
00:30:29,192 --> 00:30:31,110
I'm gonna miss you so much.

422
00:30:32,740 --> 00:30:35,233
I'm gonna miss you, too,...

423
00:30:35,425 --> 00:30:37,726
.. but we'll always stay in touch.

424
00:30:37,918 --> 00:30:40,028
You know what I'm saying.

425
00:30:40,220 --> 00:30:42,138
Howard, please.

426
00:30:42,905 --> 00:30:44,824
I have to...

427
00:30:46,357 --> 00:30:49,906
When you got that offer today
to sell the house, I...

428
00:30:50,288 --> 00:30:52,111
.. I realised suddenly...

429
00:30:53,070 --> 00:30:56,139
.. we wouldn't be sharing
those winter evenings again.

430
00:30:56,331 --> 00:31:01,221
Yeah, but you knew I was only up here
to get well, and not permanently.

431
00:31:03,044 --> 00:31:06,879
Is the difference in our ages
awkward for you ?

432
00:31:11,578 --> 00:31:13,399
I'm in love with Peter.

433
00:31:14,742 --> 00:31:16,948
Isn't that the most ridiculous thing ?

434
00:31:18,481 --> 00:31:21,742
Considering I don't think
I even have a chance with him.

435
00:31:23,372 --> 00:31:25,290
I did for a while.

436
00:31:26,633 --> 00:31:32,003
I keep telling myself that maybe
it'll still work out all right somehow.

437
00:31:34,208 --> 00:31:36,126
And why Peter and not you ?

438
00:31:38,044 --> 00:31:39,961
No reason worthy of you.

439
00:31:43,607 --> 00:31:45,716
How often I've wanted to touch you.

440
00:31:49,551 --> 00:31:51,853
Please. Please, don't.

441
00:31:53,674 --> 00:31:55,784
Now that I've embarrassed us both...

442
00:31:57,127 --> 00:32:01,730
Let me make you some coffee. You're
gonna have a terrible hangover tomorrow.

443
00:32:01,730 --> 00:32:04,606
I don't play this game that well
in the light, let alone the dark.

444
00:32:24,073 --> 00:32:25,895
Look how much it's cleared up.

445
00:32:28,293 --> 00:32:30,210
You can see a billion stars.

446
00:32:31,361 --> 00:32:33,183
It should be nice tomorrow.

447
00:32:35,772 --> 00:32:37,978
So tell me,...

448
00:32:38,170 --> 00:32:40,854
.. is it true you worked on
the atomic bomb ?

449
00:32:41,046 --> 00:32:42,772
No.

450
00:32:43,059 --> 00:32:45,169
Did Diane tell you that ?

451
00:32:45,361 --> 00:32:46,992
Yes.

452
00:32:47,183 --> 00:32:48,909
Not at all.

453
00:32:49,101 --> 00:32:53,224
I did one small, unrelated project
at Los Alamos many years ago.

454
00:32:55,238 --> 00:32:58,691
But when she's describing me to people
I'm the father of the A-bomb.

455
00:32:58,882 --> 00:33:01,567
What branch of physics
are you involved with ?

456
00:33:03,581 --> 00:33:06,553
Something much more terrifying
than blowing up the planet.

457
00:33:06,937 --> 00:33:08,567
Really ?

458
00:33:08,855 --> 00:33:12,883
Is there anything more terrifying
than the destruction of the world ?

459
00:33:13,171 --> 00:33:15,184
Yeah.

460
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:18,924
The knowledge that it doesn't
matter one way or the other.

461
00:33:19,212 --> 00:33:21,130
That it's all random.

462
00:33:22,472 --> 00:33:25,157
Originating aimlessly out of nothing and...

463
00:33:26,979 --> 00:33:28,992
.. eventually vanishing for ever.

464
00:33:31,007 --> 00:33:33,307
I'm not talking about the world.

465
00:33:33,499 --> 00:33:35,417
I'm talking about the universe.

466
00:33:36,568 --> 00:33:38,965
All space, all time, just...

467
00:33:40,597 --> 00:33:42,418
.. a temporary convulsion.

468
00:33:44,624 --> 00:33:46,445
And I get paid to prove it.

469
00:33:47,212 --> 00:33:50,472
You feel sure of that, when
you look out on a night like tonight...

470
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:54,691
.. and see all those millions of stars ?
That none of it matters ?

471
00:33:56,994 --> 00:33:59,679
I think it's just as beautiful as you do.

472
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:06,296
And vaguely evocative of some deep truth
that always just keeps slipping away.

473
00:34:08,692 --> 00:34:11,953
But then my professional
perspective overcomes me,...

474
00:34:13,295 --> 00:34:17,994
.. a less wishful,
more penetrating view of it,...

475
00:34:20,296 --> 00:34:22,692
.. and I understand it for what it truly is.

476
00:34:24,706 --> 00:34:26,529
Haphazard,...

477
00:34:27,584 --> 00:34:29,406
.. morally neutral...

478
00:34:30,940 --> 00:34:32,762
.. and unimaginably violent.

479
00:34:34,872 --> 00:34:37,940
Look, we shouldn't have
this conversation.

480
00:34:40,721 --> 00:34:42,544
I have to sleep alone tonight.

481
00:34:45,708 --> 00:34:48,010
That's why I cling to Diane...

482
00:34:48,297 --> 00:34:50,311
.. and consider myself very lucky.

483
00:34:51,557 --> 00:34:55,393
She's warm and vital
and holds me while I sleep.

484
00:34:56,927 --> 00:35:01,626
That way I don't have to dream of
photons and quarks.

485
00:35:42,573 --> 00:35:44,586
I have a question for you, Richard.

486
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:48,421
Your daughter hates me.

487
00:35:50,531 --> 00:35:52,449
Our daughter...

488
00:35:53,408 --> 00:35:55,423
.. hates me, and I love her.

489
00:35:57,148 --> 00:35:59,930
She's my one child,...

490
00:36:00,217 --> 00:36:02,422
.. and I want her to be happy.

491
00:36:06,162 --> 00:36:08,560
She never got over
the shooting, you know.

492
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:14,697
See, now, I'm a tough cookie.

493
00:36:16,135 --> 00:36:18,054
I can file and forget.

494
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:24,382
Rap once if you hear me, Richard.

495
00:36:29,176 --> 00:36:30,999
I want her to forgive me.

496
00:36:33,204 --> 00:36:36,177
So you speak to her. OK, Richard ?

497
00:36:38,861 --> 00:36:40,780
You two were so close.

498
00:36:42,314 --> 00:36:44,232
She loved you so much.

499
00:36:47,876 --> 00:36:49,794
You rap if you hear me, Richard.

500
00:36:53,534 --> 00:36:55,356
Rap, Richard.

501
00:36:57,466 --> 00:36:59,383
Rap once.

502
00:37:00,438 --> 00:37:02,260
Rap.

503
00:37:02,260 --> 00:37:05,137
I love those old songs.

504
00:37:20,192 --> 00:37:23,739
Between the music,
the candlelight and the drinks,...

505
00:37:24,027 --> 00:37:26,713
.. it feels like we're in some exotic place.

506
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,055
Mm.

507
00:37:28,343 --> 00:37:30,549
I should never drink. My head swims.

508
00:37:36,877 --> 00:37:38,699
What are you doing ?

509
00:37:39,753 --> 00:37:43,399
I've wanted to touch your face
since the first time we met.

510
00:37:43,687 --> 00:37:45,604
What do you want me to say to you ?

511
00:37:55,097 --> 00:37:58,357
Soon we'll be going
in separate directions.

512
00:37:58,549 --> 00:38:01,234
Peter, you must know
that this is impossible.

513
00:38:01,522 --> 00:38:05,933
Lane is my best friend. She's crazy about
you. I don't think I could ever do that.

514
00:38:06,221 --> 00:38:09,289
- And she's become so attached to you.
- Please.

515
00:38:10,537 --> 00:38:13,413
I already feel guilty enough
because I led her on.

516
00:38:16,098 --> 00:38:19,838
Not on purpose. I just wasn't
thinking about anyone but myself.

517
00:38:21,851 --> 00:38:24,632
She's told me about
all the time you spent together.

518
00:38:24,919 --> 00:38:29,139
I know about all your walks and talks
by the lake, under the stars.

519
00:38:29,427 --> 00:38:31,345
She's told me all that.

520
00:38:32,976 --> 00:38:34,797
I felt very lonely.

521
00:38:36,044 --> 00:38:38,824
I needed some company,
and my marriage broke up.

522
00:38:41,126 --> 00:38:44,194
I was losing confidence
that I could write this book.

523
00:38:45,153 --> 00:38:47,646
I needed a voice
to keep me from panicking.

524
00:38:49,468 --> 00:38:51,387
But you made love together.

525
00:38:52,824 --> 00:38:56,757
I didn't understand how vulnerable
she was until it was too late.

526
00:38:59,730 --> 00:39:01,647
I know it's my fault.

527
00:39:07,017 --> 00:39:11,717
Would you... Would you have become
serious about her if I hadn't come along ?

528
00:39:13,443 --> 00:39:15,648
I don't know. Maybe.

529
00:39:16,703 --> 00:39:19,867
You do funny things
when you feel empty inside.

530
00:39:20,059 --> 00:39:21,785
Look,...

531
00:39:23,415 --> 00:39:25,333
.. I'm married.

532
00:39:27,155 --> 00:39:30,799
