from camp in a week. I have a life.

533
00:39:31,087 --> 00:39:33,004
I know.

534
00:39:33,963 --> 00:39:35,785
But is it the life you want ?

535
00:39:38,566 --> 00:39:40,389
Is it ?

536
00:39:42,402 --> 00:39:46,142
- You've been flirting with me for weeks.
- Please, just go away.

537
00:40:01,485 --> 00:40:03,308
My husband's a wonderful man.

538
00:40:07,239 --> 00:40:11,362
Oh, he's bewildered
because I wanted this summer apart.

539
00:40:15,197 --> 00:40:17,306
He's a radiologist.

540
00:40:17,498 --> 00:40:20,471
He takes X-rays, but...

541
00:40:20,663 --> 00:40:24,595
.. I never let him take them of me
because, if he looked inside, he'd...

542
00:40:24,882 --> 00:40:29,198
.. he'd see things that he wouldn't
understand and he'd be terribly hurt.

543
00:40:30,636 --> 00:40:32,842
Somewhere along the line I just...

544
00:40:34,856 --> 00:40:38,020
.. I just started going through
the motions of my life.

545
00:40:43,295 --> 00:40:45,116
Steffie...

546
00:40:47,802 --> 00:40:53,075
I've just... I've just longed so
to hear certain things said to me again.

547
00:40:54,610 --> 00:40:59,212
I want so much to respond,
but I can only run.

548
00:41:01,035 --> 00:41:03,623
- Don't run.
- I can only run.

549
00:41:04,774 --> 00:41:06,691
That's all I can do.

550
00:41:11,199 --> 00:41:13,021
I knew you cared about me.

551
00:41:13,213 --> 00:41:18,008
That's why I couldn't look at you when
you were around because I felt so guilty.

552
00:41:21,747 --> 00:41:23,666
I wanna kiss you right now.

553
00:41:25,488 --> 00:41:28,653
You can't. You can't because
there's too many problems.

554
00:41:28,940 --> 00:41:30,762
This is just out of the question.

555
00:41:33,064 --> 00:41:36,132
Out of the question.
We're gonna be discovered.

556
00:41:36,324 --> 00:41:39,104
Just please go away.
It's out of the question.

557
00:42:10,558 --> 00:42:12,380
Time for me to go home.

558
00:42:13,243 --> 00:42:15,352
Sorry about the Kurosawa film.

559
00:42:17,079 --> 00:42:20,722
I made some coffee before.
D'you want me to heat it up for you ?

560
00:42:21,106 --> 00:42:23,119
No, thanks. I'd rather stay drunk.

561
00:42:26,284 --> 00:42:29,736
Maybe you'd better.
I'm supposed to work tomorrow.

562
00:42:29,928 --> 00:42:32,516
You've been in such
a strange mood all night.

563
00:42:34,339 --> 00:42:37,790
Did you know that the universe
was haphazard, morally neutral...

564
00:42:38,078 --> 00:42:40,092
.. and unimaginably violent ?

565
00:42:45,750 --> 00:42:47,572
Peter...

566
00:42:48,627 --> 00:42:50,449
What happened to us ?

567
00:42:51,887 --> 00:42:53,805
What do you mean ?

568
00:42:54,093 --> 00:42:57,546
You know, we were getting so close...

569
00:42:57,738 --> 00:43:01,285
.. and we... we shared all that time...

570
00:43:02,628 --> 00:43:04,833
.. and, um...

571
00:43:05,025 --> 00:43:07,519
.. and that night at the lake...

572
00:43:07,710 --> 00:43:11,834
I mean, did I... Am I misreading the signs ?

573
00:43:13,559 --> 00:43:15,669
Maybe you did.

574
00:43:18,545 --> 00:43:21,039
I can't let myself get involved right now.

575
00:43:24,970 --> 00:43:28,039
I'm gun-shy from my marriage and...

576
00:43:28,231 --> 00:43:31,491
.. I'm unsettled about my life, my work.

577
00:43:31,779 --> 00:43:33,601
Can I help ?

578
00:43:33,793 --> 00:43:37,916
They're my problems.
I don't wanna cause you any suffering.

579
00:43:39,354 --> 00:43:41,273
You're doing so well.

580
00:43:45,300 --> 00:43:47,410
You need to think about yourfuture.

581
00:43:48,369 --> 00:43:50,574
Yeah, I know.

582
00:43:50,862 --> 00:43:52,685
I know you're right. I...

583
00:43:53,834 --> 00:43:56,232
It's silly, but I just...

584
00:43:56,424 --> 00:44:02,848
You know, I have these dreams
that, when we're both in New York,...

585
00:44:04,191 --> 00:44:06,492
.. you know, we'd...

586
00:44:06,779 --> 00:44:08,602
I don't know.

587
00:44:09,657 --> 00:44:14,164
You know, we just... We feel things
so similarly so much of the time,...

588
00:44:14,548 --> 00:44:16,369
.. and that's so rare.

589
00:44:18,863 --> 00:44:23,274
I don't... I'm sorry, I'm really tired.
I don't know what I'm saying.

590
00:44:25,192 --> 00:44:29,987
The funny thing is that I'll probably
wind up calling you at 3am in New York...

591
00:44:30,370 --> 00:44:32,672
.. to keep me from going off the deep end.

592
00:44:32,672 --> 00:44:35,549
- Hi. Can I give you a hand there ?
- No, that's OK.

593
00:45:09,782 --> 00:45:11,893
Listen, I had a talk with Peter.

594
00:45:13,619 --> 00:45:16,399
And he doesn't wanna
get involved right now.

595
00:45:16,687 --> 00:45:18,988
And that's OK. I understand that.

596
00:45:19,180 --> 00:45:22,823
He's... You know,
he's got a lot of problems.

597
00:45:23,015 --> 00:45:27,043
But I... But maybe things
will be different later on. You know ?

598
00:45:27,426 --> 00:45:30,591
I'm glad that things are
out in the open anyway.

599
00:45:30,879 --> 00:45:32,700
You know, I do feel better.

600
00:45:33,659 --> 00:45:35,769
We'll both be living in New York.

601
00:45:36,057 --> 00:45:38,358
Who knows ? You know,
anything could happen.

602
00:45:38,358 --> 00:45:41,235
Who could that be ?

603
00:45:43,825 --> 00:45:44,880
Hello ?

604
00:45:45,072 --> 00:45:47,852
Oh, Ken. No, she's right here.
One second.

605
00:46:08,565 --> 00:46:13,167
Ken, listen. I told you the lights were out
and the phone was out. I couldn't call you !

606
00:46:13,551 --> 00:46:15,373
Right. Yes.

607
00:46:16,428 --> 00:46:20,839
I still don't know. I'm thinking about
spending some time in New York.

608
00:46:21,127 --> 00:46:24,099
Please don't bring that up now.
It's late and I'm tired.

609
00:46:24,291 --> 00:46:26,305
Let me call you tomorrow. Good night.

610
00:46:26,305 --> 00:46:29,182
Oh, God.

611
00:46:46,827 --> 00:46:48,744
I didn't know you were still here.

612
00:46:50,567 --> 00:46:52,389
I heard your voice.

613
00:47:08,498 --> 00:47:10,321
Peter, we're not alone.

614
00:47:16,074 --> 00:47:17,896
Steffie, I love you.

615
00:47:21,636 --> 00:47:23,458
From the first day.

616
00:47:43,020 --> 00:47:44,842
We could be alone.

617
00:47:48,102 --> 00:47:50,596
I can't spend the night in the guesthouse.

618
00:47:53,951 --> 00:47:55,870
Maybe not the whole night,...

619
00:47:57,500 --> 00:48:00,186
.. but we could have
some of it alone together.

620
00:48:11,021 --> 00:48:12,844
Oh, God.

621
00:48:15,432 --> 00:48:17,255
Would you ?

622
00:48:29,336 --> 00:48:31,255
Look, if...

623
00:48:32,788 --> 00:48:34,802
If this means anything to you,...

624
00:48:37,103 --> 00:48:39,693
.. I really want to, but I...

625
00:49:57,750 --> 00:50:00,339
I just love this room. It's just perfect.

626
00:50:00,531 --> 00:50:03,695
We could knock this wall out
and make one big room.

627
00:50:03,887 --> 00:50:07,914
- That's a thought.
- It's big enough as it is. I love the size.

628
00:50:08,202 --> 00:50:09,833
OK, whatever.

629
00:50:10,025 --> 00:50:12,614
- What about fishing ?
- The lake has bass, Lane told me.

630
00:50:12,902 --> 00:50:14,916
Of course, you can always stock the lake.

631
00:50:15,108 --> 00:50:18,655
It seems so inane to dump fish into a lake
just to pull 'em back out again.

632
00:50:19,039 --> 00:50:21,819
- No dumber than golf !
- Your wife's not a golfer !

633
00:50:22,011 --> 00:50:23,929
Gimme a break.

634
00:50:24,121 --> 00:50:28,150
That's Diane Frazier. I used to have such
a crush on her when I'd see her picture.

635
00:50:28,437 --> 00:50:31,218
- Diane Frazier ? Wasn't she...
- She was a model, playgirl.

636
00:50:31,410 --> 00:50:34,669
She was always at the Stork Club
or El Morocco with some tennis player.

637
00:50:34,957 --> 00:50:37,738
- Those people lead such exciting lives.
- Yes, don't they ?

638
00:50:38,121 --> 00:50:42,436
- It's gonna be great to get out of the city.
- I'm so excited about buying a dog.

639
00:50:42,820 --> 00:50:46,464
Our co-op doesn't permit dogs
and I've always wanted a pit bull.

640
00:50:46,847 --> 00:50:49,629
I'd love to go upstairs
and take some measurements.

641
00:50:49,820 --> 00:50:51,738
Lane, is it OK to go upstairs ?

642
00:50:51,929 --> 00:50:55,191
Oh, well, my mother's
still sleeping up there.

643
00:50:55,479 --> 00:50:58,643
- Really ?
- Yeah. She's a late sleeper.

644
00:50:59,027 --> 00:51:00,944
I don't think I ever slept past noon.

645
00:51:01,232 --> 00:51:03,534
- She'll be up soon.
- Maybe we could see the barn ?

646
00:51:03,725 --> 00:51:06,793
Could you show us the barn ?
I know Mr Raines has some questions.

647
00:51:06,985 --> 00:51:11,109
OK. You know where it is, don't you ?
Just follow that path out of the house.

648
00:51:11,397 --> 00:51:13,986
I'll join you in one second.
I just wanna finish up.

649
00:51:14,178 --> 00:51:15,904
- They gonna buy ?
- Looks like it.

650
00:51:16,096 --> 00:51:17,439
That's great.

651
00:51:17,630 --> 00:51:21,562
Lane, Howard called, and the stand
that sells the corn you like is open again.

652
00:51:21,754 --> 00:51:24,054
- He's gonna bring some over.
- Uh-huh.

653
00:51:25,877 --> 00:51:28,465
What's the matter ?
Why are you so depressed ?

654
00:51:31,151 --> 00:51:33,739
I just think about Peter all the time.

655
00:51:36,712 --> 00:51:39,397
Lane, just don't. Don't.

656
00:51:39,589 --> 00:51:42,466
I think he's gonna
write that book on my mother.

657
00:51:42,754 --> 00:51:43,809
God.

658
00:51:44,001 --> 00:51:47,644
They're all supposed to go out today
together. If she ever gets up.

659
00:51:47,932 --> 00:51:50,617
Oh, she's up.
She said she'd be a little late.

660
00:51:50,808 --> 00:51:53,206
- Lane, could I speak to you ?
- Yes.

661
00:51:53,398 --> 00:51:55,604
- We need you to answer some questions.
- OK.

662
00:51:55,796 --> 00:51:57,906
Their final offer is 175.

663
00:51:58,098 --> 00:52:00,111
175 ? You said two !

664
00:52:00,398 --> 00:52:03,467
That's as high as they'd go.
This area isn't what it was.

665
00:52:03,754 --> 00:52:05,960
But I've really been counting
on that money.

666
00:52:06,152 --> 00:52:08,549
- Are you sure ?
- I'm sorry.

667
00:52:32,810 --> 00:52:34,632
- - Yeah ?

668
00:52:37,797 --> 00:52:39,618
- Hi.
- Hi.

669
00:52:39,811 --> 00:52:44,509
Um, Diane said they'd be a little late.
I'll let them know that you're here.

670
00:52:54,290 --> 00:52:56,017
You've really been avoiding me.

671
00:52:56,208 --> 00:52:58,509
I think you should leave
and go back to New York.

672
00:52:58,797 --> 00:53:00,811
I'd like to know what's going on.

673
00:53:01,003 --> 00:53:05,414
I'm having a hard time and, even
though she tries to hide it, Lane is, too.

674
00:53:05,797 --> 00:53:08,578
- Don't say that.
- She thinks about you all the time.

675
00:53:08,866 --> 00:53:12,031
- And you ?
- Naturally, I think about you.

676
00:53:13,469 --> 00:53:15,291
And yet you avoid me.

677
00:53:16,058 --> 00:53:20,469
- Will you write Diane's biography ?
- Believe it or not, I'm thinking about it.

678
00:53:20,757 --> 00:53:23,154
Why ? What happened
to the book about your father ?

679
00:53:23,442 --> 00:53:25,264
I know. I...

680
00:53:26,128 --> 00:53:28,908
It just isn't coming. I told you that.

681
00:53:29,196 --> 00:53:32,744
I've been beating my brains out
about it all summer long and I...

682
00:53:33,127 --> 00:53:34,949
I don't know. It's lifeless.

683
00:53:35,717 --> 00:53:39,264
And then I hear all these sensational
anecdotes and stories. You know ?

684
00:53:39,552 --> 00:53:43,483
This woman's had an incredible life.
I mean, the shooting alone is a book.

685
00:53:43,771 --> 00:53:46,361
- Lane doesn't want it written.
- I'm not so sure.

686
00:53:46,551 --> 00:53:49,429
If I do it, I can protect her.
Somebody's gonna write it.

687
00:53:49,716 --> 00:53:53,360
Look, Peter, just put yourself
in her place for one minute.

688
00:53:53,648 --> 00:53:57,964
Here's this 14-year-old girl. Her mother
leaves her father, who Lane adored,...

689
00:53:58,347 --> 00:54:03,622
.. and moves in with this thug, who beats
up Diane, and Lane ends up shooting him.

690
00:54:04,005 --> 00:54:07,745
It's completely wrecked her life.
You don't wanna put her through it again.

691
00:54:07,936 --> 00:54:10,910
You know, people staring at her
as she walks down the street.

692
00:54:11,197 --> 00:54:12,828
I don't know.

693
00:54:16,184 --> 00:54:19,731
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry. I don't...

694
00:54:20,115 --> 00:54:23,759
I just feel so... guilt-ridden.

695
00:54:23,951 --> 00:54:25,869
I'm just very tense.

696
00:54:29,321 --> 00:54:31,431
Oh, Peter, please don't do this.

697
00:54:32,581 --> 00:54:34,307
Oh...

698
00:54:35,266 --> 00:54:36,991
Steffie.

699
00:54:40,253 --> 00:54:42,075
Let's...

700
00:54:43,609 --> 00:54:45,526
Let's go to Paris together.

701
00:54:48,308 --> 00:54:50,129
"Let's go to Paris together."

702
00:54:51,568 --> 00:54:56,076
My God. You really are
a writer, aren't you ?

703
00:54:58,377 --> 00:55:04,034
This is why I have to stay away from you.
Because you just make my head... spin.

704
00:55:04,418 --> 00:55:07,007
I just can't... I can't do this.

705
00:55:07,295 --> 00:55:09,116
I can't...

706
00:55:31,843 --> 00:55:33,666
Oh, my God.

