00:55:39,610 --> 00:55:44,597
I read about a woman bitten by a squirrel
in Central Park and she got rabies.

709
00:55:44,981 --> 00:55:47,475
Nothing like that
ever happens up here.

710
00:55:47,762 --> 00:55:51,694
What bothers me are not the
raccoons but gnats. They drive you crazy.

711
00:55:51,981 --> 00:55:55,241
You don't have a big
insect problem here, do you, Lane ?

712
00:55:55,529 --> 00:55:57,063
Lane ?

713
00:55:57,255 --> 00:56:00,036
- But you do have mosquitoes ?
- Naturally, with the pond.

714
00:56:00,228 --> 00:56:03,871
Well, mosquitoes are rare.
Aren't they, Lane ?

715
00:56:04,159 --> 00:56:06,844
- Lane ?
- It's... It's usually very pleasant.

716
00:56:07,803 --> 00:56:12,406
- I imagine the frogs'd eat the mosquitoes.
- If the snakes don't eat the frogs !

717
00:56:12,790 --> 00:56:15,091
Is it OK if we go upstairs ?

718
00:56:15,283 --> 00:56:16,913
Yes, um...

719
00:56:17,105 --> 00:56:20,173
Sorry. I'm getting a headache.
I'll rejoin you in a few minutes.

720
00:56:20,365 --> 00:56:23,338
OK, but hurry. There are many questions
Mr and Mrs Raines have.

721
00:56:23,626 --> 00:56:26,024
Yes. Now, what about hornets and bees ?

722
00:56:26,311 --> 00:56:30,051
This is the country,
Mrs Raines, not midtown Manhattan.

723
00:56:30,339 --> 00:56:32,927
Oh, my God. I just can't
believe that happened !

724
00:56:33,119 --> 00:56:36,764
- It was my fault.
- Oh, Peter, please ! I just can't handle this !

725
00:56:42,133 --> 00:56:44,339
Lane. Lane, I'm sorry.

726
00:56:45,490 --> 00:56:48,654
Lane. Lane, I'm sorry. Please forgive me.

727
00:56:49,613 --> 00:56:52,489
- Lane !
- Has this been going on long ?

728
00:56:52,777 --> 00:56:56,134
No. No ! Please. Jesus.

729
00:56:56,421 --> 00:56:59,107
- Are you in love with him ?
- It's not what you think.

730
00:56:59,490 --> 00:57:02,654
- What do you mean ?
- Lane, I just don't know what I've done.

731
00:57:02,846 --> 00:57:06,106
- I just don't know what I've...
- A lot of things make sense now.

732
00:57:06,394 --> 00:57:09,751
There's nothing to make sense.
Absolutely nothing to make sense.

733
00:57:09,943 --> 00:57:12,820
So many times I saw
you and Peter looking at each other.

734
00:57:13,204 --> 00:57:15,217
No, don't do that. Just don't do that.

735
00:57:15,313 --> 00:57:17,519
This is my fault. Stephanie's not to blame.

736
00:57:17,710 --> 00:57:20,299
- Leave us alone.
- I'm sorry you found out like this.

737
00:57:20,683 --> 00:57:23,079
There's nothing to find out.
You're making it worse.

738
00:57:23,367 --> 00:57:26,532
There's not nothing.
Let's get this out on the table.

739
00:57:26,724 --> 00:57:28,929
I want Steffie to go with me
to New York or Paris.

740
00:57:29,217 --> 00:57:33,628
Peter, the summer's over. I'm going back
to Philadelphia. I miss my children.

741
00:57:33,915 --> 00:57:37,367
I can't play these games.
I've been married too long. I just...

742
00:57:37,751 --> 00:57:40,820
I don't know what I am.
I don't know what I've done.

743
00:57:41,012 --> 00:57:44,081
I just... I'm not who I thought I was.

744
00:57:44,369 --> 00:57:47,437
I'm beginning to think
that antique fair will be too crowded.

745
00:57:47,629 --> 00:57:50,217
You're getting cold feet
about driving to East Hope.

746
00:57:50,409 --> 00:57:52,903
I am not. I just thought
today's the wrong day.

747
00:57:53,190 --> 00:57:56,739
We could postpone it. You and Peter
could work on the book around here.

748
00:57:57,027 --> 00:58:00,479
You know, Peter, I think we could do
a whole section on Las Vegas.

749
00:58:00,766 --> 00:58:04,122
I know so many great
Sammy Davis stories. He's the best.

750
00:58:04,314 --> 00:58:08,053
- Did ya tell Lane about our conversation ?
- Oh, yeah. Listen, darling.

751
00:58:08,437 --> 00:58:11,985
Lloyd and I have decided
that we wanna live here.

752
00:58:12,273 --> 00:58:14,958
This house is our idea of heaven.

753
00:58:15,246 --> 00:58:19,465
I fell in love with it the moment
I stepped inside. It was like coming home.

754
00:58:19,753 --> 00:58:24,836
I know you're off back to the city,
but whenever you wanna use it, it's yours.

755
00:58:25,219 --> 00:58:28,192
You know, weekends
or the summertime. Whenever.

756
00:58:28,479 --> 00:58:31,548
You're gonna need a sweater.
I better go up and get one.

757
00:58:31,739 --> 00:58:33,178
I don't understand.

758
00:58:33,466 --> 00:58:36,726
You know one of my first
projects ? I'm gonna put in a pool.

759
00:58:37,013 --> 00:58:41,329
I never, ever liked the pond
because there's live things in there !

760
00:58:41,617 --> 00:58:43,344
Your mother's a wonderful swimmer.

761
00:58:43,534 --> 00:58:46,220
I took her swimming in Santa Fe.
She outdid everybody.

762
00:58:46,508 --> 00:58:50,247
- She's got perfect legs for a bathing suit.
- What are you talking about ?

763
00:58:50,535 --> 00:58:52,740
We're gonna move back here.

764
00:58:52,932 --> 00:58:55,425
We've discussed it
and decided to move back here.

765
00:58:55,617 --> 00:58:59,740
Lloyd loves Vermont
and I have always loved this house.

766
00:59:00,124 --> 00:59:02,521
- And if...
- You can't move back here.

767
00:59:04,151 --> 00:59:08,370
- Why not ?
- Because I'm about to sell this place.

768
00:59:08,658 --> 00:59:10,384
- You're selling it ?
- I told you...

769
00:59:10,576 --> 00:59:14,891
- Wait a minute. Since when ?
- I've mentioned this three times at least.

770
00:59:15,179 --> 00:59:18,536
- You have ?
- Don't you ever listen to me when I talk ?

771
00:59:18,728 --> 00:59:21,316
Do you only care about
what you have to say ?

772
00:59:21,604 --> 00:59:23,330
Why are you getting so nasty ?

773
00:59:23,522 --> 00:59:26,879
I got people here right now - buyers.
They're looking at it.

774
00:59:27,167 --> 00:59:31,673
Well, Jesus, wherever they are, just go
and find them and tell them the sale is off.

775
00:59:31,961 --> 00:59:35,605
- What ?
- You can't sell it. It's gonna be our home.

776
00:59:35,988 --> 00:59:37,810
You can't tell me that now.

777
00:59:37,906 --> 00:59:40,783
What are you talking about ?
This is the family house.

778
00:59:41,071 --> 00:59:43,563
How can you sell this place ?
You don't own it.

779
00:59:43,755 --> 00:59:46,727
- Well, who owns it ?
- Uh... I do.

780
00:59:46,919 --> 00:59:50,851
Well, I mean, we do. You and me.
Your father and I bought it.

781
00:59:51,138 --> 00:59:55,742
But you gave it to me years ago. I told you
then I might sell it and divide the money.

782
00:59:56,030 --> 00:59:59,865
- You said great, you could use the cash.
- Was I sober when I gave it to you ?

783
01:00:00,249 --> 01:00:03,606
- You said it was mine.
- To live in, darling, but not to sell.

784
01:00:03,797 --> 01:00:08,208
To live in ? What does that mean ?
To maintain ? To repair ? To keep up ?

785
01:00:08,496 --> 01:00:10,031
Am I the caretaker ?

786
01:00:10,222 --> 01:00:14,825
I've said a lot of things in haste. When
it comes to practical matters, I'm a dodo.

787
01:00:15,113 --> 01:00:17,511
I can't afford to move
without selling this house.

788
01:00:17,703 --> 01:00:20,867
I've run up too many debts.
It's expensive being sick.

789
01:00:21,154 --> 01:00:25,086
- Nobody's throwing you out in the cold.
- I've been counting on this money.

790
01:00:25,469 --> 01:00:29,592
I haven't been working in two years.
I've used up everything. I've borrowed.

791
01:00:29,976 --> 01:00:32,661
Darling, it's as simple as this:
my plans have changed.

792
01:00:32,948 --> 01:00:35,058
- What ?!
- We want to settle here.

793
01:00:35,250 --> 01:00:39,662
Your father and I bought this house.
He'd have wanted it to stay in the family.

794
01:00:39,950 --> 01:00:42,442
- Can't we discuss this later ?
- You're such a phoney !

795
01:00:42,730 --> 01:00:45,702
He bought the house, not you,
and I've kept it going !

796
01:00:45,990 --> 01:00:48,867
- Lane !
- Couldn't you have just stayed away ?

797
01:00:49,155 --> 01:00:51,936
Lloyd and I are not young.
We wanna settle.

798
01:00:52,127 --> 01:00:54,909
Who knows ? Maybe we'll hate it
and in a year we'll move.

799
01:00:55,101 --> 01:00:57,402
My life is just not worth all the trouble !

800
01:00:57,594 --> 01:01:01,046
Everyone, just stop it !
Diane, Lane has been through so much.

801
01:01:01,334 --> 01:01:04,690
- Don't get angry, sweetheart.
- She doesn't care what she says to me.

802
01:01:04,977 --> 01:01:07,470
- Like I'm to blame for everything.
- You are !

803
01:01:07,662 --> 01:01:11,307
- OK, calm down.
- I'm calm, Lloyd. I am calm.

804
01:01:11,594 --> 01:01:14,471
We all make mistakes,
but what's done is done.

805
01:01:14,854 --> 01:01:18,018
And if your life didn't turn out,
don't keep accusing me !

806
01:01:18,210 --> 01:01:23,676
You're the one who pulled the trigger !
I only said what the lawyers told me to.

807
01:01:28,471 --> 01:01:31,827
- What an absurd thing to say.
- It's not absurd. It's the truth !

808
01:01:33,458 --> 01:01:36,334
I don't think this is the place
to have that discussion.

809
01:01:36,526 --> 01:01:40,362
I'm just wrecked !
And you come and go with no guilt !

810
01:01:40,650 --> 01:01:43,335
I don't wanna hear any more of this.
Stop it right now.

811
01:01:43,622 --> 01:01:46,596
It's her excuse for a life wasted,
thrown away to spite me.

812
01:01:46,883 --> 01:01:50,815
- That's not true !
- Yes ! Out of spite ! Pure spite !

813
01:01:51,102 --> 01:01:55,034
Maybe things could have been different
for me if I didn't have to go through that !

814
01:01:55,321 --> 01:01:57,814
- Excuse me. Could we see the attic ?
- Get out of here !

815
01:01:58,006 --> 01:02:00,404
- Pardon me ?
- Get out of here ! Please, just leave !

816
01:02:00,691 --> 01:02:03,472
- Diane ! Relax !
- Get out of here now !

817
01:02:03,760 --> 01:02:06,828
- Diane, just relax.
- OK, take the house.

818
01:02:07,020 --> 01:02:09,802
- I didn't realise it meant that much to you.
- That's enough.

819
01:02:10,090 --> 01:02:12,486
I said she could have the house !
Now can we go ?

820
01:02:12,678 --> 01:02:14,309
That's enough !

821
01:02:14,501 --> 01:02:19,390
There are things I might do differently
if I had them to do over, but I don't.

822
01:02:19,678 --> 01:02:22,171
My head is splitting open !

823
01:02:34,734 --> 01:02:36,556
OK, I'm sorry for all the fuss.

824
01:02:41,733 --> 01:02:43,651
We all make mistakes.

825
01:03:41,188 --> 01:03:43,585
Lane, can I have the sleeping pills back ?

826
01:03:45,023 --> 01:03:48,284
- I don't know where they are.
- They're not in the medicine cabinet.

827
01:03:48,476 --> 01:03:51,640
- What's the difference ?
- That's the stupidest thing I ever heard.

828
01:03:51,928 --> 01:03:55,189
What are you talking about,
"what's the difference" ? Where are they ?

829
01:03:55,380 --> 01:03:57,778
I have no reason to get up tomorrow.

830
01:03:57,970 --> 01:04:00,367
Then you're just gonna
have to make up a reason.

831
01:04:00,750 --> 01:04:04,202
What about your plans to move to New
York and set up a photography studio ?

832
01:04:04,490 --> 01:04:06,120
You're so damn angry.

833
01:04:06,312 --> 01:04:09,380
If I haven't made it as
a photographer by now, why would I ?

834
01:04:09,668 --> 01:04:12,832
I don't know. You'll just
have to try harder, won't you ?

835
01:04:14,750 --> 01:04:16,763
So...

836
01:04:16,859 --> 01:04:18,969
.. you and Peter are
in love with each other ?

837
01:04:19,161 --> 01:04:22,613
We just became very attracted
to each other. These things happen.

838
01:04:22,901 --> 01:04:27,696
- You knew how much I cared about him.
- It happened by itself. I didn't instigate it.

839
01:04:28,080 --> 01:04:32,970
You know, we're all up here isolated from
the world. Unpredictable things happen.

840
01:04:32,970 --> 01:04:35,847
The truth is...

841
01:04:58,094 --> 01:05:00,204
.. I flirted with Peter,...

842
01:05:00,492 --> 01:05:02,313
.. I wanted him to want me,...

843
01:05:03,656 --> 01:05:06,052
.. but I didn't think it would go very far.

844
01:05:07,491 --> 01:05:11,136
I just wanted to know
that I could be wanted.

845
01:05:12,670 --> 01:05:14,683
And he seemed very challenging.

846
01:05:14,875 --> 01:05:19,095
You know, he's very clever
and busy with his novel.

847
01:05:20,341 --> 01:05:23,602
And he's charming and smart and...

848
01:05:26,096 --> 01:05:28,684
Then slowly I began to see how...

849
01:05:32,521 --> 01:05:34,534
.. very vulnerable he is and...

850
01:05:37,698 --> 01:05:39,616
.. he's so uncertain.

851
01:05:41,725 --> 01:05:43,643
And my heart went out to him.

852
01:05:45,370 --> 01:05:47,671
And I began dreaming about him.

853
01:05:49,781 --> 01:05:52,849
What's gonna happen ?
Are you gonna go away with him ?

854
01:05:54,672 --> 01:05:56,589
I can't. No, I can't do that.

855
01:05:56,781 --> 01:06:01,192
It's... It's not so easy
when you're married with... kids.

856
01:06:03,782 --> 01:06:06,178
That's something I wouldn't know.

857
01:06:06,370 --> 01:06:08,288
Now give me those pills.

858
01:06:10,878 --> 01:06:14,618
Tomorrow will come
and you'll find some distractions.

859
01:06:15,577 --> 01:06:18,453
You'll get rid of this place.
You'll move back to the city.

860
01:06:18,741 --> 01:06:21,234
You'll work. You'll fall in love.

861
01:06:21,426 --> 01:06:24,207
And maybe it'll work out
and maybe it won't.

862
01:06:25,070 --> 01:06:29,001
But you'll find a million petty things
to keep you going,...

863
01:06:29,385 --> 01:06:32,741
.. and distractions
to keep you from focusing on the...

864
01:06:33,124 --> 01:06:35,138
On the truth.

865
01:06:35,330 --> 01:06:38,302
I don't know what the truth is
and you don't either.

866
01:06:38,590 --> 01:06:41,180
I just wanna swallow all of this Valium.

867
01:06:41,467 --> 01:06:44,441
Well, it's hard to die from Valium.
It takes about a million.

868
01:06:44,823 --> 01:06:48,660
- I'll take 'em all.
- Stop it. Stop it.

869
01:06:48,852 --> 01:06:51,344
You're behaving like a petulant child.

870
01:06:51,632 --> 01:06:55,085
If you really wanted to die,
you would have done that the last time.

871
01:06:55,277 --> 01:06:57,099
I'm so lonely.

872
01:07:02,085 --> 01:07:04,770
OK, stop it, and just give me the pills.

873
01:07:06,017 --> 01:07:08,126
You really wanna die ?

874
01:07:08,317 --> 01:07:10,044
No.

875
01:07:11,961 --> 01:07:13,975
No.

876
01:07:14,167 --> 01:07:17,619
That's my problem.
I... I always wanted to live.

877
01:07:24,620 --> 01:07:27,113
Where the hell is everybody ?

878
01:07:27,688 --> 01:07:32,003
Where is everybody ? Boy, the going
gets rough and everybody vanishes.

879
01:07:32,291 --> 01:07:34,784
Lane, we're leaving !

880
01:07:34,976 --> 01:07:38,907
Lane ! God, I hate this outfit. I look
like one of the Hundred Neediest Cases.

881
01:07:39,195 --> 01:07:40,730
You look beautiful.

882
01:07:43,415 --> 01:07:45,525
You know, I'm gonna miss this place.

883
01:07:46,772 --> 01:07:49,456
Hadn't realised how pretty it was up here.

884
01:07:50,223 --> 01:07:52,045
It's so tranquil.

885
01:07:53,196 --> 01:07:55,785
And it's been in the family for so long.

886
01:07:57,415 --> 01:08:00,100
It's the closest thing
I can think of to roots.

887
01:08:02,497 --> 01:08:04,319
It might have been nice.

888
01:08:06,140 --> 01:08:08,346
Dear, it's my age talking.

889
01:08:09,978 --> 01:08:11,511
Never mind.

890
01:08:11,799 --> 01:08:13,526
Never mind. It's not in the cards.

891
01:08:13,813 --> 01:08:15,922
Palm Beach will be fine.

892
01:08:16,210 --> 01:08:18,896
The place is unimportant
as long as we're together.

893
01:08:19,086 --> 01:08:20,909
Oh, Lloyd.

894
01:08:21,101 --> 01:08:23,785
Lane, we're leaving for Palm Beach.

895
01:08:23,977 --> 01:08:26,472
If you need me,
we're staying with the Chasens.

896
01:08:26,759 --> 01:08:30,786
And let's not have a wake over what
happened before. It's over and done with.

897
01:08:31,170 --> 01:08:34,142
Life's too short
to dwell on our tragedies. Right ?

898
01:08:35,293 --> 01:08:38,553
Besides, I'm sure we all
said things we're sorry for.

899
01:08:39,416 --> 01:08:41,431
We're all temperamental.

900
01:08:41,621 --> 01:08:44,499
Otherwise, we wouldn't
all be so fascinating.

901
01:08:47,087 --> 01:08:49,101
I'm sorry if I caused you any grief.

902
01:08:50,635 --> 01:08:52,649
OK ? I wasn't thinking.

903
01:08:52,937 --> 01:08:55,335
Oh, well. It's over now.

904
01:08:57,253 --> 01:08:58,979
Lane,...

905
01:08:59,171 --> 01:09:01,184
.. you always liked this,...

906
01:09:01,376 --> 01:09:03,678
.. and I want you to keep it.

907
01:09:03,966 --> 01:09:05,787
Stephanie,...

908
01:09:06,075 --> 01:09:07,513
.. this is for you.

909
01:09:07,801 --> 01:09:11,062
I saw you admiring it
and I'd love you to have it.

910
01:09:11,254 --> 01:09:13,459
Thank you.

911
01:09:13,746 --> 01:09:15,761
Jesus ! Look at my hands.

912
01:09:16,816 --> 01:09:21,898
Now, really, I am too young for liver spots.
Maybe I could merge them into a tan.

913
01:09:22,185 --> 01:09:23,911
What do you think ?

914
01:09:24,103 --> 01:09:27,171
- Can I help with the bags ?
- Oh, my God ! I forgot.

915
01:09:27,363 --> 01:09:31,869
Howard, just in time to say goodbye and
help with the luggage. I'll get the door.

916
01:09:32,253 --> 01:09:36,568
Lloyd, put that hanging piece on top,
I beg you. Everything'll be mussed.

917
01:09:36,856 --> 01:09:39,255
Thanks, Howard.
Terrific. The door's open.

918
01:09:39,446 --> 01:09:42,706
Lane, let them get it, honey.
Come here. Come here.

919
01:09:43,090 --> 01:09:47,021
Now... No, never mind. You know where
we're gonna be, with the Chasens,...

920
01:09:47,405 --> 01:09:51,624
.. so if you need me for anything - your
hair looks just darling down like that -

921
01:09:52,008 --> 01:09:53,925
.. you call me. D'you hear me ? OK.

922
01:09:54,021 --> 01:09:56,995
And tell Peter that
I've got to rethink my memoirs.

923
01:09:57,283 --> 01:09:59,871
If I come up with a fresh approach,
then I'll call him.

924
01:10:00,063 --> 01:10:01,885
Goodbye. Be a good girl.

925
01:10:02,077 --> 01:10:05,241
Oh, God. Have you got my make-up kit ?
It's got my diaphragm in it.

926
01:10:05,433 --> 01:10:08,885
Isn't it silly ? I still travel with it.
It's like a lucky charm.

927
01:10:09,269 --> 01:10:12,529
Maybe I should donate it
to the antique fair !

928
01:10:22,022 --> 01:10:23,844
Will I see you again ?

929
01:10:28,160 --> 01:10:30,077
I think you should leave.

930
01:10:30,844 --> 01:10:33,722
I'm going to stay with Lane
and then go back home.

931
01:10:39,667 --> 01:10:43,311
It's funny. You meet somebody
under strange circumstances.

932
01:10:47,243 --> 01:10:50,791
You fall in love and then
you go off in separate directions.

933
01:10:51,941 --> 01:10:54,434
Peter, please don't make this hard for me.

934
01:10:55,489 --> 01:10:57,694
- Please.
- I feel so empty.

935
01:11:01,626 --> 01:11:06,708
You haven't even gone yet and I feel like
I've lost something I'll never find again.

936
01:11:06,708 --> 01:11:09,586
I'm so disappointed in myself.

937
01:11:21,189 --> 01:11:23,011
Steffie.

938
01:11:29,819 --> 01:11:32,409
Time will pass
and you'll forget this summer.

939
01:11:35,861 --> 01:11:37,778
And you ? Will you forget it ?

940
01:11:41,422 --> 01:11:43,244
I'll try.

941
01:11:44,683 --> 01:11:46,504
It won't be easy, but I'll try.

942
01:12:13,547 --> 01:12:17,287
Now she's off to Palm Beach
as though nothing had happened.

943
01:12:22,368 --> 01:12:24,478
Well, I really should be going, too.

944
01:12:25,725 --> 01:12:27,451
My debts.

945
01:12:27,738 --> 01:12:29,561
I have to manage the final sale.

946
01:12:31,574 --> 01:12:33,492
All the details.

947
01:12:37,807 --> 01:12:40,780
Lane, I want so badly
to tell you not to worry.

948
01:12:41,068 --> 01:12:42,698
Howard.

949
01:12:42,986 --> 01:12:46,822
And that I'll take care of you,
that nothing would make me happier.

950
01:12:48,068 --> 01:12:50,657
I've gotten so used to
having you in my life.

951
01:12:52,192 --> 01:12:56,508
- You're all that gives it meaning now.
- Howard, don't. Don't.

952
01:12:57,563 --> 01:12:59,096
- I'm sure that...
- I can't.

953
01:12:59,288 --> 01:13:01,110
.. when you leave here...

954
01:13:02,836 --> 01:13:04,754
.. I'll never see you again.

955
01:13:07,247 --> 01:13:09,069
But I really did grow to love you.

956
01:13:12,712 --> 01:13:14,535
Lane.

957
01:13:16,740 --> 01:13:18,562
I came to say goodbye.

958
01:13:21,534 --> 01:13:24,796
I think it's better
if I head back to the city tonight.

959
01:13:25,083 --> 01:13:26,905
You haven't finished your book.

960
01:13:29,686 --> 01:13:31,508
It's finished.

961
01:13:33,234 --> 01:13:35,056
What a sad tone in your voice.

962
01:13:38,603 --> 01:13:40,906
I loved all the time we spent together.

963
01:13:44,358 --> 01:13:47,618
And I appreciate your faith in me and...

964
01:13:49,632 --> 01:13:51,454
.. the encouragement.

965
01:13:54,235 --> 01:13:56,344
I'm sorry I couldn't live up to it.

966
01:14:04,303 --> 01:14:06,029
Well...

967
01:14:07,659 --> 01:14:09,578
Take care of her, Howard.

968
01:14:09,578 --> 01:14:12,455
- Hi.
- Hi.

969
01:15:14,306 --> 01:15:16,032
Would you like some tea ?

970
01:15:16,224 --> 01:15:17,854
No.

971
01:15:25,046 --> 01:15:27,251
- It's chilly.
- Yeah.

972
01:15:28,114 --> 01:15:30,416
It was chilly when I got up this morning.

973
01:15:38,470 --> 01:15:41,060
In a few days it'll be September.

974
01:15:41,252 --> 01:15:43,170
I know.

975
01:15:44,225 --> 01:15:47,101
There are so many things to do,
selling a house.

976
01:15:49,882 --> 01:15:52,184
It'll keep you busy. That's good.

977
01:15:54,965 --> 01:15:56,883
When do you have to go home ?

978
01:15:58,225 --> 01:16:00,815
In a couple of days I'll go back.

979
01:16:01,006 --> 01:16:04,170
The kids need school supplies
and new shoes.

980
01:16:06,568 --> 01:16:08,773
- Sweet kids.
- Yeah.

981
01:16:13,760 --> 01:16:15,678
Oh, Steffie.

982
01:16:19,321 --> 01:16:23,157
Soon you'll leave here and
you'll start all over again in New York.

983
01:16:25,459 --> 01:16:28,336
There'll be a million things
to keep you busy.

984
01:16:31,500 --> 01:16:33,418
It's gonna be OK.

